title: Iron Maiden - Doubled- Live at Reading 80 and BBC Rock Show 79
description:
Iron Maiden - Doubled- Live at Reading and BBC Fri. Rock Show(2-CD) 1979-80 ak320

You seemed to like the Foreigner Double Shot and Im always ready to keep a good idea rolling...
So now we got Iron Maiden Live at Reading Fest 1980 and a BBC Friday Rock Show from
1979

Tracklist

Recorded live at Reading Festival, Reading, England, 23/08/1980

1. The Ides of March
2. Wrathchild
3. Sanctuary
4. Prowler
5. Remember Tomorrow
6. Killers
7. Running Free
8. Transylvania
9. Phantom of the Opera
10. Iron Maiden
11. Drifter

Players
    Reading Festival, 23 August 1980

    Paul Di'Anno – vocals
    Steve Harris – bass
    Dave Murray – guitar
    Dennis Stratton – guitar
    Clive Burr – drums


Disk 2 Bonus Show BBC 1 Friday Rock

BBC Archives is a live album by the British heavy metal band Iron Maiden, released on 4 November 2002 as part of the Eddie's Archive box set. It is a collection of songs from three live shows and one live radio broadcast, recorded by the BBC between 1979 and 1988

1. 	"Iron Maiden" 	  	3:46
2. 	"Running Free" 	Paul Di'Anno, Harris 	3:10
3. 	"Transylvania" 	  	4:03
4. 	"Sanctuary" 	Di'Anno, Harris, Dave Murray 	3:45

They are doubled but im sure Maiden listeners want them . I know I did I searched for awhile 
to find em. Its all.... Paul Di'Anno. He was good for the brief time except some of the live gigs (tours) there were some problems with Booze and Dope but what the hey its Rock N Roll....

Players

BBC Rock  Show
    Paul Di'Anno – vocals
    Steve Harris – bass
    Dave Murray – guitar
    Tony Parsons – guitar
    Doug Sampson: drums
